title: Request: allow excluding built-in tools from the agent sandbox
body: |
  ## Problem

  Flue's `createAgent()` and `createSandboxSessionEnv()` provide a set of built-in
  tools (`read`, `edit`, `bash`, `grep`, `glob`, `task`). Currently there is no
  public API to opt out of specific built-in tools. The only workaround is to
  hijack the internal `createBuiltinTools` prototype method and filter by name:

  ```ts
  const original = proto.createBuiltinTools;
  proto.createBuiltinTools = function (...args) {
    const tools = original.apply(this, args);
    return tools.filter((t) => t.name !== 'task');
  };
  ```

  This is fragile — it depends on internal method naming and structure.

  ## Requested API

  Something like one of:

  - `excludeTools: string[]` on agent runtime config or sandbox options
  - `tools: { include?: string[]; exclude?: string[] }` on sandbox options
  - A callback on `AgentProfileSchema` that can filter the resolved tool list

  ## Use case

  The app uses its own custom task/subagent orchestration via `tools-archive/`
  and doesn't want the AI to see Flue's default `task` tool, which adds
  redundant/confusing options for the LLM.

  Flue version: 0.9.2
